# No shims · no stubs · no tech-debt allowances

**NOT ALLOWED. NOT ALLOWED. NOT ALLOWED.**

Agents must not introduce shims, stubs, placeholders, deferred work, or “tech debt OK” carve-outs. Ship the real implementation, or stop and ask — never leave a fake.

## Forbidden (product / app / package / script code)

- Files or modules named / acting as `shim`, `stub`, `placeholder`, `noop`, `fake`, `dummy`, `temp`
- Empty or throw-only implementations: `notImplemented`, `NotImplementedError`, `throw new Error("TODO")`, `// stub`, `// shim`
- Comments that excuse incompleteness: `tech debt`, `for now`, `temporary`, `workaround`, `ship later`, `fix later`, `TODO: implement`, `FIXME` as a plan to skip work
- Dual paths, compatibility layers, or “thin wrappers” that avoid doing the real cutover
- Docs or ADRs that **authorize** new shims/stubs/tech debt (except recording a ban)
- Saying “acceptable debt”, “leave a stub”, or “shim for convenience”

## Required behavior

1. Implement the real behavior end-to-end in this change, **or**
2. Stop, tell the user what is blocked, and wait for an explicit written exception in **this** turn.

Do not invent exceptions. Do not “park” work behind a stub and call the task done.

## Narrow exceptions (only these)

| Exception | Rule |
|-----------|------|
| User letter this turn | User explicitly ordered a named temporary exception **in this chat turn** |
| Test doubles | `*.test.*`, `*.spec.*`, `**/testing/**`, `**/__mocks__/**` only |
| Deprecation register | Existing **redirect-only** / archive rows already listed — do not add product UI; do not create **new** shim/stub surfaces |
| Mentioning the ban | Rules/hooks/docs that state this prohibition |

## Hook enforcement

`preToolUse` → `.cursor/hooks/no-shim-stub-tech-debt.mjs` denies Write/StrReplace/EditNotebook payloads that introduce forbidden patterns. Do not rename, encode, or split edits to bypass the hook.
